SIMPLE: petrify
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Petrify
<hw>Pet"ri*fy</hw> <pr>(p⟦ecr⟧t"r⟦icr⟧*f⟦imac⟧)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Petrified</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>;
<pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Petrifying</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>petra</ets> rock, Gr.
<grk>pe`tra</grk> (akin to <grk>pe`tros</grk> a stone) + <ets>-fy</ets>:
cf. F. <ets>p⟦eacute⟧trifier</ets>. Cf. <er>Parrot</er>,
<er>Petrel</er>, <er>Pier</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To convert, as
any animal or vegetable matter, into stone or stony substance; <as>as,
<ex>petrified</ex> wood</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A river that <qex>petrifies</qex> any sort of wood or leaves.</q>
<rj><qau>Kirwan.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make callous or obdurate; to transform, as by
petrifaction; <as>as, to <ex>petrify</ex> the heart</as>.
<xex>Young</xex>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Petrifying</xex> accuracy.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And <qex>petrify</qex> a genius to a dunce.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A hideous fatalism, which ought, logically, to <qex>petrify</qex>
your volition.</q> <rj><qau>G. Eliot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To paralyze, especially with fear; to stupefy;
<as>as, she was <ex>petrified</ex> by the sight of the bear in her
tent</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>The poor, <qex>petrified</qex> journeyman, quite unconscious of
what he was doing.</q> <rj><qau>De Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Petrify</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Petrify
<hw>Pet"ri*fy</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To become stone,
or of a stony hardness, as organic matter by calcareous
deposits.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: To become stony, callous, or
obdurate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Like Niobe we marble grow,⟦br⟧
And <qex>petrify</qex> with grief.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Petrine</ent>⟦br⟧
